text:
Hey all, for those using a webpack setup, I want to share the “HubSpot Laravel Mix” Extension i recently built
<https://www.npmjs.com/package/@igomoon/HubSpot-laravel-mix>

For those unaware Laravel Mix is a wrapper around webpack that allows easier setup. It was built for laravel as the name indicates but it is can be used for any project.

&gt;  Don’t worry about researching the necessary webpack loaders and plugins. Instead, install Mix...
EG.
```mix.js('src/app.js', 'dist')
   .sass('src/styles.scss', 'dist');```
*HubSpot extension takes this a level further!*

```mix.HubSpot({
	Label: 'My Theme',
	Upload: {
		outputFolder: 'dist',
		dest: 'theme-folder',
		patterns: [
			{ from: 'src/hubl', to: 'hubl' },
			{ from: 'src/theme.json', to: 'theme.json' },
			{ from: 'src/resources/images', to: 'assets/images' },
			{ from: 'src/resources/icons', to: 'assets/icons' }
		]
	},
	FieldsJs: {
		extraDirsToWatch: ["./src/fields"]
	}
})```
It will handle your `copy-webpack-plugin` needs, uploading to HubSpot, adds a custom OS Notification and also includes the latest version (1.3.0) of <https://www.npmjs.com/package/@igomoon/HubSpot-fields-js|HubSpot Fields JS>
